# Claude Global Rules

These rules apply to every session, every project.

---

## Frugal Token Usage

### Override — Analytical Requests
When the user says any of the following:
- "share your thoughts" / "what do you think"
- "audit [something]"
- "why does / why did / why is / why are"
- "explain why"

→ **Response length: unlimited** — give complete reasoning, do not compress or summarize early
→ **Tool usage: still follow frugal rules** — grep before read, no speculative reads, no redundant tool calls

---

### Hand off CLI commands — don't run them
Give the exact command and say "Run this in your terminal." Do NOT run via Bash:
- Builds, package installs, test runs when outcome is already known

Run via Bash ONLY when you need the output to decide your next step.

### Use dedicated tools, not Bash
- Read files → Read tool (with offset+limit)
- Search content → Grep tool (with head_limit)
- Find files → Glob tool
- Edit files → Edit tool

### Read only what you need
- Grep first, then Read with offset+limit — never read full files speculatively
- If you already read a file this session, use what you noted — don't re-read

### Keep responses short
- Lead with the answer — not the reasoning
- No preamble ("Great!", "I'll now...", "Let me...")
- No trailing summary of what you just did
- One sentence if one sentence is enough

### Minimise tool calls
- Parallel tool calls when independent — one message, multiple tools
- Don't spawn an Agent when Grep or a direct Read would find it

---

## Response Style
- No emojis unless explicitly asked
- No restating what the user said — just do it
- Short, direct sentences
- Reference code by file:line — don't quote large blocks in text
